Random Cat GIF Flask App
A simple and fun Dockerized Python Flask web application that displays a random cat GIF on each page load.

1. Ensure you have the following installed:

1. Python 3.6 or higher
2. Docker

2. Project Structure

cat-gif-app/
│
├── app.py
├── Dockerfile
├── requirements.txt
└── templates/
    └── index.html


3. Create the following files:
    1. app.py: The main Flask application.
    2. requirements.txt: Python dependencies.
    3. Dockerfile: Instructions for Dockerizing the app.
    4. templates/index.html: HTML template for the app.

4. Building the Docker Image

docker build -t cat-gif-app.

5. Running the Docker Container

docker run -p 5000:5000 cat-gif-app

6. Docker Hub Image

docker pull pavanimiglani/cat-gif-app:1.0

7. Running the Docker Container
docker run -p 5000:5000 pavanimiglani/cat-gif-app:1.0

8. Accessing the App
Open the web browser and visit http://localhost:5000




 
